3/*++
4/* NAME
5/* tls_proxy_print
6/* SUMMARY
7/* write DSN structure to stream
8/* SYNOPSIS
9/* #include <tls_proxy.h>
10/*
11/* int tls_proxy_context_print(print_fn, stream, flags, ptr)
12/* ATTR_PRINT_MASTER_FN print_fn;
13/* VSTREAM *stream;
14/* int flags;
15/* void *ptr;
16/* DESCRIPTION
17/* tls_proxy_context_print() writes a TLS_SESS_STATE structure
18/* to the named stream using the specified attribute print
19/* routine. TLS_SESS_STATE() is meant to be passed as a call-back
20/* to attr_print(), thusly:
21/*
22/* ... SEND_ATTR_FUNC(tls_proxy_context_print, (void *) tls_context), ...
23/* DIAGNOSTICS
24/* Fatal: out of memory.
25/* LICENSE
26/* .ad
27/* .fi
28/* The Secure Mailer license must be distributed with this software.
29/* AUTHOR(S)
30/* Wietse Venema
31/* IBM T.J. Watson Research
32/* P.O. Box 704
33/* Yorktown Heights, NY 10598, USA
34/*--*/
35
36#ifdef USE_TLS
37
38/* System library. */
39
40#include <sys_defs.h>
41
42/* Utility library */
43
44#include <attr.h>
45
46/* Global library. */
47
48#include <mail_proto.h>
49
50/* TLS library. */
51
52#include <tls.h>
53#include <tls_proxy.h>
54
55/* tls_proxy_context_print - send TLS session state over stream */
56
57int tls_proxy_context_print(ATTR_PRINT_MASTER_FN print_fn, VSTREAM *fp,
58 int flags, void *ptr)
59{
60 TLS_SESS_STATE *tp = (TLS_SESS_STATE *) ptr;
61 int ret;
62
63#define STRING_OR_EMPTY(s) ((s) ? (s) : "")
64
65 ret = print_fn(fp, flags | ATTR_FLAG_MORE,
66 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_PEER_CN,
67 STRING_OR_EMPTY(tp->peer_CN)),
68 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_ISSUER_CN,
69 STRING_OR_EMPTY(tp->issuer_CN)),
70 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_PEER_CERT_FPT,
71 STRING_OR_EMPTY(tp->peer_cert_fprint)),
72 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_PEER_PKEY_FPT,
73 STRING_OR_EMPTY(tp->peer_pkey_fprint)),
74 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_PEER_STATUS,
75 tp->peer_status),
76 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_CIPHER_PROTOCOL,
77 STRING_OR_EMPTY(tp->protocol)),
78 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_CIPHER_NAME,
79 STRING_OR_EMPTY(tp->cipher_name)),
80 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_CIPHER_USEBITS,
81 tp->cipher_usebits),
82 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_CIPHER_ALGBITS,
83 tp->cipher_algbits),
84 ATTR_TYPE_END);
85 return (ret);
86}
87
88#endif
